A lorry driver has been charged with the manslaughter of 39 people found dead inside a refrigerated trailer, Essex Police have said. Maurice Robinson, 25, was arrested after the bodies of 31 men and eight women were found in Grays on Wednesday. He is further charged with people trafficking, immigration and money laundering offences, the force said. Mr Robinson, of Laurel Drive, Craigavon, is due before Chelmsford Magistrates' Court on Monday.